      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity study",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions compared across k-omega SST, realizable k-epsilon, and Reynolds Stress Model (RSM). Maximum inter-model spread in NIH: 12.4%. k-omega SST selected as best-compromise model based on PIV agreement and computational cost. RSM overpredicts by 8.1% relative to bench mean.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/ev-05-turbulence-sensitivity-study",
      "wasAttributedTo": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-cfd-lab"
